FBIS3-51033 "drlat008_c_94012" FBIS-LAT-94-008 Document Type:Daily Report 12 Jan 1994 MEXICO Chiapas Crisis Correction to Army Asked for Advance Warning on Bombings PA1001024594 PA1001024594 Article Type:BFN The following corrections pertain to the item headlined "Indians Asks for Advanced Warning on Bombings," published in the 10 January Latin America DAILY REPORT, pages 18-19: Page 19, first paragraph, second sentence, reads... at dusk on 6 January and grew more intensely on the morning of 7 January... (correcting dates, and rewording) Same page, ninth paragraph, reads... During this apparent offensive, the Army recovered control of a majority of towns, including Huixtan, Oxchuc, and Altamirano, that were abandoned by the guerrillas without pressure from the military... (rewording)
